    "en": {
      "title": "Two people who went to look at cattle were killed by wild elephants",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Welikanda and Aralagangwila Police said that two people in Dimbulagala and Welikanda, Dimbulagala Divisions who went to see cattle died in the attacks of wild elephants on the night of the 21st.",
        "The police say that Sarath Palitha, an unmarried man, and Bandula Dissanayake of Welikanda Dimbulane Dissanayake Mudiansela, thirty-seven years old, were killed in a wild elephant attack in Aralagangwila Kandegama Pradesh."
      ],
